title: Good breakfast- Great staff
text: Enjoyed a breakfast with a great staff(Melanie was quite helpful). All were efficient especially with outside seating and providing refills as needed. Priced reasonably for the area.

title: Good Meal - But Over-Priced
text: The House Special was tasty. Grilled shrimp and steak tips. Could use some gravy to prevent dryness. Enjoyed the cole slaw. Fish chowder had too much flour, but tasty. Drinks were good sized.

title: Great Find in Center of Town
text: Great fresh pizza - fresh toppings (meat and veggie)on a thin crust. One of the best I’ve tasted. Sandwiches were also enjoyed with amounts that could be shared. A good experience even in the pandemic times

title: Delightful stay in the Center of Town
text: Wonderful experience in a Classic New England structure. Accommodating staff during a pandemic was not phased. Room amenities were wonderful and the entire stay was enjoyable. Would return again. Sorry we stayed only one night.

title: Jody, the Lady Leslie Reef Fishing Leader
text: Reef fishing with Jody was a great time. Catching was even better! A joyous and happy half day of snapper and mackerel on the hook was ended with fillets that would be frozen and brought home to be enjoyed. A plan for next year was already secured.

title: A Must on Secret Beach
text: The food was outstanding the lounging atmosphere and activities make this the place to go when visiting the Secret Beach. Not to be missed!

title: The Right Belize Breakfast
text: Estel’s offers the Belize breakfast your looking for. Wonderful simple meals with the fry jacks that want me to return year after year.

title: Rewarded Again
text: A second visit was rewarded again with real good poppers and a tasty house special stir-fry. The atmosphere is easy to low key and friendly.

title: Try the Octapus
text: A wonderful choice was a octopus appetizer that was a surprise experience. Was a delightful different and most pleasing taste. Soft and tasty in garlic.

title: A Great Place to Enjoy a Vacation
text: Year after year, Casa Maya makes a vacation a great experience, The staff is always the best representatives of the approach of the management. Special dinners were a new twist that made for a delightful time.

title: Best Meal-Best View
text: A great snapper meal, on the pier, on the water. Great atmosphere with the action around us. Even the cheesecake was a great topper.

title: The Best Professional Experience
text: Every time a gracious, elegant delight. The food, the attention, the extreme attention to detail makes the evening memorable. The snapper, the lobster bisque and the Moscato wine made for a dining pleasure.

title: A Fun Time
text: True Mexican spirit with fun and a meal that met expectations. The poppers were tasty. A good time was had by all.

title: A Bit of a Disappointment
text: Early on, a wine glass, not seen, was spilled behind a too large menu. You would expect a professional classy approach to refilling the glass. None was attempted. From there, the grouper fish meal which was pricy and not as tasty as expected, left me disappointed. One of the few dinners I felt they could have done better.

title: Mérida at its Best
text: A second visit to a family that makes travel an experience that is not forgotten. The rooms as really beautiful and the variety of breakfasts every morning are outstanding. Yoa and Ron- Thank you for a great week. See you next year.

title: Small restaurant with Great Choices
text: Really loved the fresh fish ( grouper) and the cheese cake dessert. Staff was as entertaining as the Santa Lucia music.

title: Pleasant Surprise Fusion
text: Wonderful combination of Peruvian and Asian ingredients and tastes made for a delightful meal. Don’t forget the desserts.

title: A Hole in the Walk Delight
text: A small narrow corridor serving wonderful Cuban favorites. Tasty boiled chicken, plantains, rice and beans was everything to remember about Cuban food.

title: Seaside Delight
text: The grilled fish was excellent with rice, black beans and salad. Great atmosphere on the beach. The Lime pie was a pleasant surprise.

title: Great views and Tasty Meal
text: The view of Mykonos harbor was outstanding from the outdoor seating. Wonderful meal at reasonable pricing.

title: Saganshi was tasty.
text: Wonderful panoramic views of Santorini buildings. Seating was spectacular and the service was quick and efficient. Take the cable car.

title: Uncovered city of Knossos
text: Birthplace of Minoan civilization uncovered. Many rooms that should be done by guided tour for best understanding

title: Spectacular Tour of Meteora Monesteries
text: Bus tour of 2 hours from Volos to Monasteries of Meteora. Spectacular views not to be missed. Can be difficult for even slightly handicapped.
place: Panoramic Meteora and all Monasteries Tour from Kalabaka

title: Hotel & Restaurant by the Sea
text: The restaurant was a fine meal with a tour group. The hotel looked like a fancy reminder of times past. The fish was excellent and the family of cats left nothing to waste. The trek down from a large parking area on a narrow cobblestone road was difficult for anyone with disabilities. Be sure to drive down to the wonderful old seaside village.

title: Historical and Attentive to Detail
text: The visit to many historical sites along with a tour of European and Asian sides was a half day historical view of the area.

title: Nighttime Cruise with Show
text: A nighttime cruise was a wonderful pictorial experience with added dinner of small amounts of Turkish foods. The fish was tasty. The show was a variety of local folklore.
place: Bosphorus Dinner Cruise with Turkish Night Show from Istanbul
